title: ‘KPop Demon Hunters’ Singers Reveal Their Wildest ‘Pinch Me’ Moments of 2025 After a Truly ‘Golden’ Year
summary: Charlie Puth, Demi Lovato and more also shared memories of the past 12 months with Billboard.
body: Arguably no one had a more golden year than the stars of KPop Demon Hunters — and in an interview with Billboard ahead of their performance on Dick Clark’s New Year’s Rockin’ Eve with Ryan Seacrest , HUNTR/X singers REI AMI, EJAE and Audrey Nuna opened up about which moments from the past 12 months shined the brightest.  Related HUNTR/X (AUDREY NUNA, EJAE & REI AMI), Zara Larsson, Demi Lovato & More Reveal Their Top 2025 Moments & More | Billboard News Chappell Roan, Mariah Carey & More Set for Expanded ‘Dick Clark’s New Year’s Rockin’ Eve’ Special HUNTR/X’s ‘Golden’ Fends Off Holiday Competition to Reach No. 1 on Billboard’s Radio Songs Chart In the video published Tuesday (Dec. 30) — just one day before the trio is set to take the stage in New York City’s Times Square to help usher viewers into 2026 — the voices behind Netflix’s fictional girl group struggled to name just one “pinch me” moment to define their 2025. “This whole year was a ‘pinch me’ year,” remarked EJAE. “For me it was the Macy’s Thanksgiving Day parade,” Ami said, referencing the ladies’ …
